<div
  x-data="{ toggle_edit_description: false }"
  class="mt-8">
  <div class="flex items-center">
    <div class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-700">Description</div>
    <button 
      @keydown.window.escape="toggle_edit_description = false" 
      x-show="!toggle_edit_description" 
      @click="toggle_edit_description = true" 
      type="button" 
      class="ml-2 inline-flex items-center px-2 py-1 border border-transparent text-xs font-medium rounded text-blueGray-700 bg-blueGray-100 hover:bg-blueGray-200 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-indigo-500">
      Edit description
    </button>
  </div>
  <div 
    x-show="!toggle_edit_description" 
    class="mt-1.5 propse prose-sm w-full">
    <p>Provides similar capabilities to Phoenix's built-in live_patch/2 function. When navigating to the current LiveView, handle_params/3 is immediately invoked to handle the change of params and URL state. Then the new state is pushed to the client, without reloading the whole page. For live redirects to another LiveView, use LiveRedirect instead.</p>
  </div>
  <div 
    x-show="toggle_edit_description" 
    @click.away="toggle_edit_description=false" 
    x-transition:enter="ease-out duration-300" 
    x-transition:enter-start="opacity-0 translate-y-4 sm:translate-y-0 sm:scale-95" 
    x-transition:enter-end="opacity-100 translate-y-0 sm:scale-100" 
    x-transition:leave="ease-in duration-200" 
    x-transition:leave-start="opacity-100 translate-y-0 sm:scale-100" 
    x-transition:leave-end="opacity-0 translate-y-4 sm:translate-y-0 sm:scale-95" 
    class="mt-1.5 propse prose-sm w-full">
    <form>
      <label for="task_note" class="sr-only">Type a description for the task</label>
      <textarea id="task_note" class="block w-full h-20 text-sm transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out border-gray-300 rounded-md shadow-sm focus:ring-indigo-500 focus:border-indigo-500"></textarea>
      <div class="flex mt-2 items-center space-x-3 justify-end">
        <button type="button" @click = "toggle_edit_description = false" class="btn-secondary">Cancel</button>
        <button type="submit" class="btn-primary">Create</button>
      </div>
    </form>

  </div>
</div>